    "Scott_D_Alessandro: exactly! When installing n, it performs the npm config set prefix underneath the hood for you so you don't have to do it manually, it installs everything to a User/username/n directory.  Good to know. Thanks. Everything is working fine for now with my current setup but n is looking like a very good option to consider.",
