    "const type = (arg) =&gt; {   let stringAsArray = Object.prototype.toString     .call(arg)     .split(' ');   return stringAsArray[1]     .slice(0, stringAsArray[1].length-1); }  Since the string output from Object.prototype.toString is two words when passing an object, I split them into an array and used the second index to access the string name of the type, and used slice to return everything except the last character (to get rid of the trailing ']').  Your code is very compact and clear :).",
