    "Hiya,  My Test'em is failing when I stringify(fnc). The error is \"Expected 'function() {}' to equal 'function () {}'.\"  By the looks of it the initial fnc variable is initialised as:  var fnc = function() {},  But the stringify(fnc) results expects:  expect(stringify(fnc)).toEqual('function () {}');  Am I missing something with my solution or is there some extra whitespace in the spec? My function part of stringify():  stringify(){ if (['Boolean', 'Number', 'Function'].includes(type(input))) {     return input.toString();   } }  Cheers",
